A toggle synchronizer is used to pass single event pulses between clock domains regardless of whether the transfer is slow-to-fast or fast-to-slow. The source domain converts the pulse into level toggle. The destination domain synchronizes the level, then uses edge detection to recreate the pulse.

### Potential Issues
