This module models a 256-word classic BRAM. In the `initial` block, it utilizes a `for` loop to mathematically initialize every single memory word dynamically across the array to a continuous sequential offset based on index `(i * 3) + 5`.

### Potential Issues
1. **Synthesis File-Size Bloat (Elaboration Unrolling)**: When synthesizing this RTL, the synthesis tool evaluates `initial` blocks in software memory beforehand. It calculates the value for all 256 locations manually. The tool then natively unrolls the array into a hardcoded matrix mapped directly into the BRAM IP core `.INIT` parameter fields. This maps perfectly for a highly compressed bitstream geometry.
